SERVICE CORPORATION INTERNATIONAL Revenue and Financial Data

   Service Corporation International (SCI) is to death what H&R Block is to taxes. SCI, the largest funeral and cemetery services company in North America, operates about 1,535 funeral homes and 469 cemeteries in 45 US states, eight Canadian provinces, the District of Columbia, and Puerto Rico. The company's primary services include embalming, burial, and cremation. As part of its business, SCI also sells traditional funeral necessities, including prearranged funeral services, caskets, burial vaults, cremation receptacles, flowers, and burial garments. The company has expanded significantly in recent years through acquisitions and is aggressively pursuing the cremation market.
  







